### Critique
1. In the unit tests, I made an error in the test data format by using strings instead of string vectors for the input of the `event_scheduler` function. The function expects a vector of tuples, but in the unit tests, I provided a vector of strings, which caused a parsing error.

### Improve
1. Modify the unit tests to correctly provide a vector of tuples as the input for the `event_scheduler` function.

```julia using Dates, Test

@testset "event_scheduler" begin
    @test event_scheduler([]) == "No events"
    @test event_scheduler([("2023-02-02 10:30", "2023-02-02 11:30"), ("2023-02-02 11:00", "2023-02-02 12:00")]) == "No conflicts"
    @test event_scheduler([("2023-02-02 10:30", "2023-02-02 11:30"), ("2023-02-02 11:00", "2023-02-02 12:00"), ("2023-02-02 10:45", "2023-02-02 11:45")]) == "Conflict at event (2023-02-02 10:45, 2023-02-02 11:45)"
end

```
